# 4. 思い起こすはあの日の

Airi: I wasn't expecting the place to be so crowded that we'd be asked to share a table.
Ena: Ugh... Why do I have to start off the new year by eating pancakes with you?
Akito: If you don't wanna stay, then you're free to leave. I'll have the ones you ordered.
Ena: What? I am not leaving. I've also been looking forward to having them.
Waiter: Thank you for your patience. I have three plates of our limited pancakes, and the toasted sandwich drink set.
Toya: Thank you. I ordered the sandwich set. The pancakes are for these three.
Ena: Wow, these look amazing...!
Ena: Talk about photogenic! They clearly put a lot of effort into these toppings, and they're so colorful!
Airi: There's apparently white bean paste inside the pancakes. I'm really looking forward to this!
Toya: I see... So this is how they're making these pancakes look like kagami mochi...
Ena: Hehe. First, I'm gonna take some pics...
Akito: You're taking more pictures...?
Akito: Anyway... I'm gonna have these while they're still hot.
Akito: So, let's eat.
Akito: (These are good...)
Akito: (I thought it'd be a lot sweeter since they covered this whole thing in white chocolate, but the fruit's acidity is doing a good job of balancing it out.)
Akito: (I definitely wouldn't mind getting more.)
Toya: You seem to like them very much.
Akito: Hm? Yeah, I do.
Airi: You get the pictures you wanted, Ena?
Ena: Yeah! Check it out. Don't they look amazing?
Airi: Yeah, they do! These look better on your screen than they do in real life!
Airi: I know you're good at taking selfies, but you've become such a great photographer. I might have you take pictures of me sometime.
Ena: No problem! I feel like I know how to make you look the cutest, Airi!
Airi: Hehe. Then, I'll be looking forward to our shoot!
Akito: (Those two really are close.)
Akito: (But it still feels kinda weird that Ena has such a good friend.)
Akito: (As far as I know, Momoi's had Ena's best interests at heart ever since they first met.)
Akito: (Not only do they hang out like this, she's always been there to listen and cheer Ena up.)
Akito: (Including that time...)
Junior High School Akito: Hey, how long do you plan on staying cooped up in there?
Junior High School Akito: You can always try talking to Dad again about your future. For now, you should at least have something to eat...
Junior High School Ena: Shut up! This has nothing to do with you!
Junior High School Akito: Nothing to do with me? Do you know how worried Mom is about you right now...?!
Junior High School Ena: I said stop talking! Just go away!!
Junior High School Akito: ...
Junior High School Akito: *Sigh*
Junior High School Akito: Seriously, how long do I have to keep putting up with this...?
Junior High School Akito: (Yeah, I get that she's mad at Dad for what he said about her future as an artist...)
Junior High School Akito: (But she has to know that she can't keep sulking forever.)
Junior High School Akito: (She's been leaving her art crap out in the hallway lately, and any time anyone tries to talk to her she starts throwing things.)
Junior High School Akito: (I should probably just wash my hands of the whole thing.)
Junior High School Akito: (Not like she's going to listen to anything I—)
???: Oh...! Akito!
Junior High School Akito: Huh?
Junior High School Akito: Momoi...? What are you doing here?
Junior High School Airi: Oh, so... I've actually been looking for you, Akito. There's something I'd like to discuss with you...
Junior High School Airi: Sorry, I know this is really sudden. But Ena told me a little while back that you like to hang out in this area.
Junior High School Akito: I see..
Junior High School Akito: So, what is it that you'd like to discuss...?
Junior High School Airi: Yeah, so...
Junior High School Airi: How's Ena doing...?
Junior High School Akito: What?
Junior High School Airi: She's just been kind of weird lately.
Junior High School Airi: I haven't been able to talk to her much lately because of work, and she clams up whenever I ask if something's wrong.
Junior High School Airi: Which is why I was hoping that you could tell me more, Akito.
Junior High School Airi: I know I should wait until she's ready to tell me... But I'm worried about her...
Junior High School Akito: Oh, I see...
Junior High School Airi: So, is she okay?
Junior High School Akito: ...
Junior High School Akito: Not exactly... Some stuff happened with our folks, and she's been kind of a mess ever since...
Junior High School Airi: Your parents?
Junior High School Airi: Wait a second... Did she get into a fight with your dad about her future?
Junior High School Airi: She's been acting strange ever since we got those surveys regarding our plans for the future... So I figured that was probably it.
Junior High School Akito: ...
Junior High School Airi: I'm sorry... I know I'm being really nosy.
Junior High School Airi: Hey, Akito...
Junior High School Airi: Can you do me just one favor?
Junior High School Akito: A favor?
Junior High School Airi: Yes. I know this is asking a lot of you, and this is going to sound really weird.
Junior High School Airi: But...
Junior High School Airi: I want you to keep an eye on Ena for me.
Junior High School Airi: Ena won't tell me anything.
Junior High School Airi: Every single time I ask her about what happened between her and your guys' dad, she just says, “Nothing...”
Junior High School Airi: Or even, “You made your dream come true, Airi, so you keep going...”
Junior High School Akito: ...
Junior High School Airi: Ena was a huge part of me becoming an idol, but I haven't been able to give back at all. It feels like I haven't been there for her...
Junior High School Airi: I know this might not sound right coming from me but...
Junior High School Airi: I don't have anyone else that I can rely on like that... I don't think Ena does either...
Junior High School Airi: So please... I need you to look after her...
Junior High School Akito: ...
Junior High School Akito: Why do you care about her so much, Momoi?
Junior High School Airi: What?
Junior High School Akito: You're an idol. You're someone special.
Junior High School Akito: So, why are you hanging out with someone as selfish as her...?
Junior High School Airi: Because she's my best friend, and I owe her a lot.
Junior High School Akito: You owe her?
Junior High School Airi: Yeah.
Junior High School Airi: Like I mentioned, she helped me get closer to my dream.
Junior High School Airi: When I appeared on this one variety show a little while back, one of my classmates decided to make fun of me.
Junior High School Airi: That was when Ena stepped in to help me.
Junior High School Airi: It's not like they said anything that terribly mean.
Junior High School Airi: But I was relieved to find out that others out there were willing to stand up for me.
Junior High School Airi: Even now... She's stuck between a rock and a hard place herself, but she told me to keep doing my best as an idol.
Junior High School Airi: She's been a huge source of support...
Junior High School Airi: She's helped me so much until now. So, I can't just stand idly by while she suffers.
Junior High School Akito: She really did those things...?
Junior High School Akito: (She owes Ena this...)
Junior High School Akito: (I sort of get what Momoi's trying to say... Also...)
Junior High School Akito: (She cares this much about Ena's well-being.)
Junior High School Akito: (Which means...)
Junior High School Akito: (I shouldn't be so quick to abandon her.)
Akito: (Compared to back then, Ena's like a different person now.)
Akito: (To be fair, making music as a group with Akiyama and the others has played a big role...)
Akito: (But so has Momoi.)
Akito: (And it seems like Momoi's been staying in regular contact with her...)
Akito: (Come to think of it, I haven't had a chance to talk to her about what happened back then.)
Akito: (I should try to thank her the next chance I get.)
